===README===

Steps before you can work with it:

1. Install Android SDK and set the ANDROID_HOME Environment Variable to this location
2. install the cordova jar --> see libs
3. If Eclipse: install ADT plugin and m2e android connector
4. make a symbolic link in the assets folder to the Zapfmaster shared modules:
*Windows:cd to assets folder, then: mklink /D webapp "c:\...\gitrepoFolder\Zapfmaster2000\src\zapfmaster2000-service\src\main\webapp"
*Mac/linux: make a symlink to the above folder with ln -s ~/git/Zapfmaster2000/src/zapfmaster2000-service/src/main/webapp webapp

5.Then you can either use
*maven:
mvn clean install android:deploy android:run
or
*Eclipse:
rightclick on project-> run as -> Android Application

Step 4 is not necessary if you only use maven!

6. Congratulations! Keep  zapfing ;)